------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project implements an inverse pendulum - a robotic device which sole purpose is to stay upright. Angular frequency is measured by a
gyroscopic sensor, the data are then processed in a ARM Cortex M0+ MCU where a simple PID control loop is implemented. The MCU then drives a 
stepper motor to balance the pendulum. A Bluetooth module can be used for PC communication. The MCU is bare metal. The project includes schematic
and PCB design in Altium, code design and finally a physical realization.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Project folders:

/codes - C codes for the MCU

/pcb - PCB and schematic source codes
